## GameEngine Details (`game/GameEngine.ts`)

### Tick loop (50 ms / 20 TPS)
```
processInputs → updateBombs → updateExplosions → checkItemPickups
→ checkWinCondition → computeDiff → onTick(diff)
→ if winner: stop() + onGameOver(winner)
```

### Movement
- Sub-tile positions: `pixelX`, `pixelY` in tile-unit floats
- `delta = PLAYER_SPEED * speedMultiplier * DT` (~0.15 tiles/tick at full speed)
- AABB collision with `HALF = 0.45` half-width; corners rounded to nearest tile
- Slide mechanic: try X+Y → X only → Y only (critical for Bomberman feel)
- Own-bomb passthrough: player's current rounded tile is exempt from BOMB
  collision so they can walk away from a just-placed bomb

### Bomb placement
- Only if `activeBombs < maxBombs` and tile is EMPTY or ITEM
- Sets grid tile to `TileType.BOMB`; increments `activeBombs`

### Bomb detonation (`detonateBomb`, recursive up to depth 8)
1. Remove bomb from grid/state, decrement owner's `activeBombs`
2. `calculateExplosionTiles` → `affectedTiles` + `destroyedSoftWalls`
3. Destroy soft walls (grid → EMPTY)
4. Mark all `affectedTiles` as `TileType.EXPLOSION`
5. Roll item drops for each destroyed soft wall (30% chance, BOMB_UP/FIRE_UP/SPEED_DOWN)
   — items are tracked in `state.items`; grid tile stays EXPLOSION until it clears
6. Kill any alive player whose `Math.round(pixelX/Y)` is in explosion set
7. Chain: collect bomb candidates in explosion set, recurse

### Explosion clear (`updateExplosions`)
- On expiry (`endsAt`): for each tile, restore to `ITEM` if an item lives there,
  else `EMPTY`

### Item pickups (`checkItemPickups`)
- Each tick: check if any alive player's rounded tile matches an item position
- Effects: `BOMB_UP` +1 maxBombs, `FIRE_UP` +1 blastRadius,
  `SPEED_DOWN` → 0.7× speed for 5 s

### Win condition
- Solo (1 player total): game over when player dies
- Multiplayer: game over when ≤ 1 alive; winner is last survivor or null (draw)

### State diff (`computeDiff`)
- Grid: element-wise compare vs `prevState`; emit only changed indices
- Players: field-by-field compare; emit only changed `Partial<Player>` (omitted
  fields not set to `undefined` — `exactOptionalPropertyTypes` compliant)
- Bombs/explosions/items: new keys vs prevState + removed keys

