## RoomManager Details (`rooms/RoomManager.ts`)

### Lifecycle FSM
```
WAITING → (room:start) → STARTING [3 s countdown]
        → IN_GAME [tick loop running]
        → GAME_OVER [3 s] → WAITING
```

### Key behaviours
- Room ID: 8-char uppercase UUID prefix (e.g. `A3F9C12B`)
- Spawn index assignment: first available slot 0–3 (corners)
- Creator transfer: if creator leaves, next player in map becomes creator
- Room destroyed when last player leaves (countdown cancelled, engine stopped)
- DB writes are fire-and-forget; server continues even if MongoDB is down
- `queueInput` is the only hot-path method — no try/catch, no DB access

