## TypeScript Strict Mode Notes

- `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`: all array reads checked for `undefined` before use;
  `SPAWN_POSITIONS[slot.spawnIndex] ?? { x: 1, y: 1 }` for variable index
- `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`: diff fields are only assigned when present (never
  set to `undefined`); `speedDebuffUntil` assigned `number | null` directly
- `noPropertyAccessFromIndexSignature`: all `Record<string, T>` accessed via
  bracket notation
- `delete` on object keys uses `// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-dynamic-delete`
  to suppress the lint warning on intentional dynamic deletes

